    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Transparent, whitish veil clouds with a fibrous (hair-like) or smooth appearance. A sheet of cirrostratus which is very extensive, nearly always ends by covering the whole sky. A milky veil of fog (or thin stratus) is distinguished from a veil of cirrostratus of a similar appearance by the halo phenomena which the sun or the moon nearly always produces in a layer of cirrostratus.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
